The paper discusses a mathematical model for capturing and distinguishing the latent structure in the articulation of questions, which is a key step in a machine-driven question-answering system. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science, which is cs.CL. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural auto-encoders, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions optimization formulations, which are relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Neural Networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.NE, in that order.
